The paper focuses on the design of datasets for visual question answering, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of the dataset design on the performance of learning models, which is related to artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Additionally, the paper proposes automatic procedures to remedy design deficiencies, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques.
